<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.214031>
    dc:description "FIGURE 3. Aporcelaimellus castaneanus sp. n. A: Anterior region in median view. B: Same in lateral, surface view. C: Female, posterior body region. D: Female, anterior genital branch. E: Pharyngeal expansion. F: Male, posterior body region. G: Male, entire body. H: Female, entire body. I: Spicule and lateral guiding piece. J: Vagina." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/214031/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.214032>
    dc:description "FIGURE 4. Aporcelaimellus castaneanus sp. n. (LM). A: Female, entire. B: Male, entire, C, D: Anterior region in median, lateral view. E: Neck region. F: Lip region in lateral, surface view. G: Female, anterior genital branch. H: Male, posterior body region. I: Cardia. J: Vagina. K: Male, spicules and caudal region. L: Male, caudal region. M: Female, caudal region. (Scale bars: A, B = 500 µm; C, I, L, M = 20 µm; D, F, J = 10 µm; E, G, H = 100 µm; K = 50 µm)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/214032/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

